# Faith Traits
Birthmark				KEY:Birthmark_Trait				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.SpecialQuality	DESC:You were born with a strange birthmark that looks very similar to the holy symbol of the god you chose to worship later in life.																																																																																																															SOURCEPAGE:p. 12
Caretaker				KEY:Caretaker_Trait				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.SpecialQuality	DESC:As the child of an herbalist or an assistant in a temple infirmary, you often had to assist in tending to the sick and wounded.																																																																																BONUS:SKILL|Heal|1|TYPE=Trait																		CSKILL:Heal								SOURCEPAGE:p. 12
Child of the Temple		KEY:Child of the Temple_Trait			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.SpecialQuality	DESC:You have long served at a temple in a city, and not only did you pick up on many of the nobility's customs, you spent much time in the temple libraries studying your faith.																											STACK:NO	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:NUMCHOICES=1|SKILLSNAMED|Knowledge (Nobility and Royalty)|Knowledge (Religion)																												BONUS:SKILL|Knowledge (Nobility and Royalty),Knowledge (Religion)|1|TYPE=Trait									CSKILL:LIST								SOURCEPAGE:p. 12
Devotee of the Green		KEY:Devotee of the Green_Trait		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.SpecialQuality	DESC:Your faith in the natural world or one of the gods of nature makes it easy for you to pick up on related concepts.																																					STACK:NO	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:NUMCHOICES=1|SKILLSNAMED|Knowledge (Geography)|Knowledge (Nature)																														BONUS:SKILL|Knowledge (Geography),Knowledge (Nature)|1|TYPE=Trait												CSKILL:LIST								SOURCEPAGE:p. 12
Ease of Faith			KEY:Ease of Faith_Trait				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.SpecialQuality	DESC:Your mentor, the person who invested your faith in you from an early age, took steps to ensure that you understood that what powers your divine magic is no different than that which powers the magic of other religions.																																																																	BONUS:SKILL|Diplomacy|1|TYPE=Trait																	CSKILL:Diplomacy							SOURCEPAGE:p. 12
History of Heresy			KEY:History of Heresy_Trait			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.SpecialQuality	DESC:You were raised with heretical views that have made it not only difficult for you to accept most religious beliefs, but you also have had to live with the fact that you or those you love were often treated as pariahs.																																																																																																SOURCEPAGE:p. 12
Indomitable Faith			KEY:Indomitable Faith_Trait			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.SpecialQuality	DESC:You were born in a region where your faith was not popular, yet you never abandoned it.																																																																						BONUS:CHECKS|Will|1|TYPE=Trait																																											SOURCEPAGE:p. 12
Sacred Conduit			KEY:Sacred Conduit_Trait			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.SpecialQuality	DESC:Your birth was particularly painful and difficult for your mother, who needed potent divine magic to ensure you survived; your mother may or may not have survived. In any event, the magic infused you from an early age, and you now channel divine energy with greater ease than most.																																																																						BONUS:VAR|TurnCheckUndead|2|TYPE=Trait										SOURCEPAGE:p. 12
Sacred Touch			KEY:Sacred Touch_Trait				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.SpecialQuality	DESC:You were exposed to a potent source of positive energy as a child, perhaps by being born under the right cosmic sign, or maybe because one of your parents was a gifted healer.																																																																																																							SOURCEPAGE:p. 12
Scholar of the Great Beyond	KEY:Scholar of the Great Beyond_Trait	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.SpecialQuality	DESC:Your great interests as a child did not lie with current events or the mundane-- you have always felt out of place, as if you were born in the wrong era.																														STACK:NO	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:NUMCHOICES=1|SKILLSNAMED|Knowledge (History)|Knowledge (The Planes)																														BONUS:SKILL|Knowledge (History),Knowledge (The Planes)|1|TYPE=Trait											CSKILL:LIST								SOURCEPAGE:p. 12

# Magic Traits
Classically Schooled		KEY:Classically Schooled_Trait		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.SpecialQuality	DESC:Your apprenticeship or early education was particularly focused on the direct application of magic.																																																																																					BONUS:SKILL|Spellcraft|1|TYPE=Trait																	CSKILL:Spellcraft							SOURCEPAGE:p. 12
Dangerously Curious		KEY:Dangerously Curious_Trait			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.SpecialQuality	DESC:You have always been intrigued by magic, possibly because you were the child of a magician or priest. You often snuck into your parent's laboratory or shrine to tinker with spell components and magic devices, and often caused quite a bit of damage and headaches for your parent as a result.																																																					BONUS:SKILL|Use Magic Device|1|TYPE=Trait																CSKILL:Use Magic Device						SOURCEPAGE:p. 12
Focused Mind			KEY:Focused Mind_Trait				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.SpecialQuality	DESC:Your childhood was either dominated by lessons of some sort (be they musical or academic) or by a horrible home life that encouraged your ability to block out distractions to focus on the immediate task at hand.																																																																		BONUS:SKILL|Concentration|1|TYPE=Trait																CSKILL:Concentration						SOURCEPAGE:p. 13
Gifted Adept			KEY:Gifted Adept_Trait				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.SpecialQuality	DESC:Your interest in magic was inspired by witnessing a spell being cast in a particularly dramatic method, perhaps even one that affected you physically or spiritually.																												STACK:NO	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:NUMCHOICES=1|SPELLS|SPELLTYPE=Arcane|SPELLTYPE=Divine									BONUS:CASTERLEVEL|SPELL.%LIST|1																																																	SOURCEPAGE:p. 13
